Note:
Runa Advanced Standard Library: Reflection Module

Provides advanced, production-grade reflection for runtime and compile-time introspection, dynamic invocation, and metadata/annotation access. Supports robust type/value introspection, metadata, dynamic method/property invocation, error handling, and validation. All code and comments follow Runa conventions.
:End Note

Note: Reflection Types and Interfaces
Type called "ReflectionContext":
    config as ReflectionConfig
    stats as ReflectionStats
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ReflectionConfig":
    enable_runtime_reflection as Boolean
    enable_compile_time_reflection as Boolean
    enable_dynamic_invocation as Boolean
    ai_mode as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "ReflectionStats":
    total_introspections as Integer
    total_invocations as Integer
    total_errors as Integer
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "Reflectable":
    type_info as TypeInfo
    value as Any
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type called "TypeInfo":
    type_id as String
    type_kind as String
    size as Integer
    alignment as Integer
    is_primitive as Boolean
    is_reference as Boolean
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Type ReflectionError is Exception with:
    message as String
    metadata as Dictionary[String, Any]

Note: Core Reflection Functions
Process called "reflect_type" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns TypeInfo:
    If value is Integer:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "Integer", type_kind as "primitive", size as 8, alignment as 8, is_primitive as true, is_reference as false, metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is Float:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "Float", type_kind as "primitive", size as 8, alignment as 8, is_primitive as true, is_reference as false, metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is Boolean:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "Boolean", type_kind as "primitive", size as 1, alignment as 1, is_primitive as true, is_reference as false, metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is String:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "String", type_kind as "reference", size as 24, alignment as 8, is_primitive as false, is_reference as true, metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is List:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "List", type_kind as "collection", size as 24, alignment as 8, is_primitive as false, is_reference as true, metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is Dictionary:
        Return TypeInfo with type_id as "Dictionary", type_kind as "collection", size as 32, alignment as 8, is_primitive as false, is_reference as true, metadata as dictionary containing
    Return TypeInfo with type_id as "Unknown", type_kind as "unknown", size as 0, alignment as 0, is_primitive as false, is_reference as false, metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "reflect_value" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns Reflectable:
    Let info be reflect_type with context as context and value as value
    Return Reflectable with type_info as info, value as value, metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_metadata" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    If value is Dictionary and value contains "metadata":
        Return value["metadata"]
    If value is Reflectable:
        Return value.metadata
    Return dictionary containing

Process called "get_annotations" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns List[Annotation]:
    If value is Dictionary and value contains "annotations":
        Return value["annotations"]
    If value is Reflectable and value.metadata contains "annotations":
        Return value.metadata["annotations"]
    Return list containing

Process called "invoke_method" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any and method_name as String and args as List[Any] returns Any:
    If not context.config.enable_dynamic_invocation:
        Raise ReflectionError with message as "Dynamic invocation is disabled" and metadata as dictionary containing
    If value is Dictionary and value contains method_name:
        Let method be value[method_name]
        If method is Function:
            Return method with args as args
        Raise ReflectionError with message as "Property '" plus method_name plus "' is not callable" and metadata as dictionary containing
    Raise ReflectionError with message as "Method '" plus method_name plus "' not found" and metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "get_property" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any and property_name as String returns Any:
    If value is Dictionary and value contains property_name:
        Return value[property_name]
    If value is Reflectable and value.value is Dictionary and value.value contains property_name:
        Return value.value[property_name]
    Raise ReflectionError with message as "Property '" plus property_name plus "' not found" and metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "set_property" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any and property_name as String and new_value as Any returns None:
    If value is Dictionary:
        Set value[property_name] to new_value
        Return None
    If value is Reflectable and value.value is Dictionary:
        Set value.value[property_name] to new_value
        Return None
    Raise ReflectionError with message as "Property '" plus property_name plus "' not found or not settable" and metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "list_methods" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns List[String]:
    If value is Dictionary:
        Return [key for key in value if value[key] is Function]
    If value is Reflectable and value.value is Dictionary:
        Return [key for key in value.value if value.value[key] is Function]
    Return list containing

Process called "list_properties" that takes context as ReflectionContext and value as Any returns List[String]:
    If value is Dictionary:
        Return [key for key in value if value[key] is not Function]
    If value is Reflectable and value.value is Dictionary:
        Return [key for key in value.value if value.value[key] is not Function]
    Return list containing 